In gobot/robot.go, around line 134, func (r *Robot) Start() calls r.Work().  If r.Work() does not return then Start will hang.  If this hangs then func (r *Robots) Start() will also hang and not call Start on any further Robots.  The solution is to make the call a goroutine.  Patch attached below.

diff --git a/robot.go b/robot.go
index 8775e87..131fade 100644
--- a/robot.go
+++ b/robot.go
@@ -131,7 +131,7 @@ func (r *Robot) Start() (errs []error) {
    }
    if r.Work != nil {
        log.Println("Starting work...")
-       r.Work()
-       go r.Work()
  }
  return
  }

